TextEng: Well met, friend. Fine night in the inn, eh. Right busy, it is.
Text: 반갑소, 친구. 선술집에서 좋은 밤이군. 꽤 바쁘네.

TextEng: Good on you. See you around.
Text: 잘 가시오. 또 보자고.

TextEng: All right then. Farewell.
Text: 그럼 됐소. 안녕히.

TextEng: Good riddance to bad rubbish.
Text: 쓰레기가 알아서 사라지니 좋군.

TextEng: Can you understand my answers? You seem a bit slow.
Text: 내 대답을 이해할 수 있소? 좀 느린 것 같은데.

TextEng: I've the time, sure enough. What do you want to know?
Text: 시간은 있소. 뭘 알고 싶소?

TextEng: Eh, if you make it quick.
Text: 에, 빨리만 하면.

TextEng: Bah, make it quick and get lost.
Text: 쳇, 빨리하고 꺼져.

TextEng: Well, just look around you. Bloodsailors looking all rough, some auction thing taking too long, and damned if I have seen any Bloodsailor brass here all night.
Text: 글쎄, 주변을 둘러보시오. 핏빛 항해자들이 험악해 보이고, 경매인지 뭔지가 너무 오래 걸리고, 밤새 핏빛 항해자 간부를 한 명도 못 봤소.

TextEng: Their business ain't my concern, especially their infighting... I really shouldn't say any more. I don't swim well, especially in a sack filled with rocks.
Text: 그들 일은 내 관심사가 아니오, 특히 내분은... 더 말해선 안 되겠소. 난 수영을 잘 못하거든, 특히 돌이 가득 찬 자루에서는.

TextEng: Nobody seems to know what was going to happen here. Vengaul Bloodsail himself was organizing it, but he's late. It may be cancelled.
Text: 여기서 뭐가 일어날지 아는 사람이 없는 것 같소. 벵골 블러드세일 본인이 주관하는 건데, 늦고 있소. 취소될지도 모르오.

TextEng: Well, concentrate hard and maybe you'll remember what I say.
Text: 글쎄, 열심히 집중하면 내 말을 기억할 수 있을지도.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Success]</Start> I suppose you're right. They are probably too busy to worry about me telling tales anyway.
Text: <StartCheck>[성공]</Start> 당신 말이 맞는 것 같소. 어차피 그들은 내가 이야기하는 걸 걱정할 만큼 한가하지 않을 거요.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> Sorry, but I'm just not getting involved. Callik wants to challenge Vengaul, that's his business, not mine and not yours.
Text: <StartCheck>[실패]</Start> 미안하지만, 끼어들고 싶지 않소. 칼릭이 벵골에게 도전하고 싶다면, 그건 그 사람 일이지, 내 일도 당신 일도 아니오.

TextEng: What do you want? Come on now, I've got time if you're quick.
Text: 뭘 원하시오? 자, 빨리만 하면 시간 있소.

TextEng: Go on, why are you bothering me? I've no interest in you.
Text: 가시오, 왜 귀찮게 하는 거요? 당신한테 관심 없소.

TextEng: No, and I don't care to. I ain't even thinking about it. Of course, I guess I showed up here... well, we're all here for strange reasons.
Text: 아니, 알고 싶지도 않소. 생각도 안 하고 있소. 물론, 나도 여기 왔긴 했지만... 뭐, 다들 이상한 이유로 여기 온 거겠지.

TextEng: Ain't much anywhere now. Plague shut most things down. I suppose you can ask, but there ain't much I can tell you.
Text: 지금은 어디든 별거 없소. 역병 때문에 대부분 문 닫았소. 물어볼 수야 있겠지만, 말해줄 게 별로 없소.

TextEng: Will my answers help? You sound like you would get lost a lot.
Text: 내 대답이 도움이 될까? 자주 길을 잃을 것 같은데.

TextEng: The Golden Apple? A fine little tavern. Not much happens there, though. The Seedy Tavern is where you want to be for action.
Text: 황금 사과? 괜찮은 작은 선술집이오. 하지만 거기선 별일 없소. 뭔가 있길 원하면 허름한 선술집이 맞소.

TextEng: Eh, it's the only place that's doing any business now. Lots of this and that, though most of the black market stuff there ends up here.
Text: 에, 지금 영업하는 유일한 곳이오. 이것저것 많은데, 거기 암시장 물건 대부분은 결국 여기로 오지.

TextEng: Eh, you'll be stuck shopping here or the Twenty in a Quiver. Most other places are gone because of the plague.
Text: 에, 여기 아니면 '스무발 화살통'에서 쇼핑할 수밖에 없을 거요. 다른 곳 대부분은 역병 때문에 없어졌소.

TextEng: This place? This is where everything happens. It's where they usually set up the black market, but things are a little strange right now.
Text: 여기요? 모든 일이 벌어지는 곳이오. 보통 암시장이 열리는 곳인데, 지금은 좀 이상하오.

TextEng: There's still the Golden Apple and the Twenty in a Quiver. A couple other places, I guess. I just stay here at the Seedy, myself.
Text: 아직 황금 사과랑 '스무발 화살통'가 있소. 다른 곳도 몇 군데 있을 거요. 난 그냥 여기 허름한 선술집에 있소.

TextEng: All right. Where did you want to ask about?
Text: 알겠소. 어디에 대해 물어보고 싶소?

TextEng: The Golden Apple is in the northwest of the district if you are interested. That puts it southwest of here.
Text: 황금 사과는 관심 있으면 지구 북서쪽에 있소. 여기서 남서쪽이겠군.

TextEng: It's a little southeast of the Seedy Tavern here. Kinda middle northeast of the district, I guess.
Text: 여기 허름한 선술집에서 약간 남동쪽이오. 지구의 중간 북동쪽쯤 되려나.

TextEng: You'll have to go to the City Core if you are looking for things like temples and mage towers.
Text: 신전이나 마법사 탑 같은 걸 찾으면 도시 중심부로 가야 하오.

TextEng: Well, I suppose there's not really any harm in me talking with you. I can just lay low a while if I get myself in trouble.
Text: 글쎄, 당신과 얘기해도 해될 건 없을 것 같소. 문제가 생기면 잠시 숨어 있으면 되지.

TextEng: Ugh... no thank you, madam, I really am not interested in... discussing this with you. If Callik wants to challenge Vengaul, that's his business.
Text: 으... 괜찮습니다, 아가씨, 정말 이것에 대해... 얘기하고 싶지 않소. 칼릭이 벵골에게 도전하고 싶다면, 그건 그 사람 일이오.

TextEng: I suppose I could say a few things. I'll just lay low for a while after so I don't get in trouble.
Text: 몇 가지 말할 수 있을 것 같소. 나중에 문제 안 생기게 잠시 숨어 있으면 되지.

TextEng: You are a pretty one, aren't you. Not the brightest star in the sky, but still a sparkler. I'll talk with you a while.
Text: 꽤 예쁘군, 그렇지. 하늘에서 가장 밝은 별은 아니지만, 그래도 반짝이는군. 잠깐 얘기하지.

TextEng: The Bloodsailors weren't always a rough group to deal with, but things have changed. Callik isn't letting Vengaul's decisions go unchallenged anymore.
Text: 핏빛 항해자가 항상 다루기 힘든 집단은 아니었소, 하지만 상황이 바뀌었소. 칼릭이 더 이상 벵골의 결정을 그냥 넘기지 않고 있소.

TextEng: I heard that there was a plague cure for sale. Rumors were all over, and I think some people were afraid the guards would hear.
Text: 역병 치료제가 팔린다고 들었소. 소문이 퍼졌고, 경비병들이 들을까 봐 무서워하는 사람들도 있었소.

TextEng: I don't know how they didn't. It was like Vengaul wanted them to know. He's flashy. A risk taker. Some of his men don't like it.
Text: 어떻게 안 들었는지 모르겠소. 벵골이 알리고 싶어한 것 같았소. 과시하기 좋아하거든. 위험을 감수하는 자요. 부하들 중 일부는 그게 마음에 안 들어하오.

TextEng: All of his plans usually involve getting as much notice as possible. He's more concerned with image than profit. That doesn't please some of his men.
Text: 그의 계획은 보통 최대한 주목받는 걸 포함하오. 이익보다 이미지에 더 신경 쓰거든. 그게 부하들 일부를 불쾌하게 하오.

TextEng: Ah, the well-loved leader and founder of the Bloodsailors. Well, not so well-loved these days, I hear. See, he likes to show off.
Text: 아, 핏빛 항해자의 사랑받는 지도자이자 창립자요. 글쎄, 요즘은 그리 사랑받지 못한다고 들었소. 보시오, 과시하기 좋아하거든.

TextEng: I hear he's been getting some trouble from his officers. They want to be a little more rough, and a lot less flashy.
Text: 부하 간부들한테 좀 문제가 생겼다고 들었소. 그들은 좀 더 거칠고, 훨씬 덜 화려하길 원하오.

TextEng: Callik... well, Callik is not a nice man. He's much more concerned with gold than he is with any show of bravado or style.
Text: 칼릭은... 글쎄, 칼릭은 좋은 사람이 아니오. 허세나 스타일보다 금화에 훨씬 더 관심이 많소.

TextEng: He's very efficient getting gold out of his victims, but he's a hard man to work for. If not for Vengaul, he'd be even worse.
Text: 피해자들에게서 금화를 뽑아내는 데 아주 효율적이지만, 모시기 힘든 사람이오. 벵골이 아니었으면 더 심했을 거요.

TextEng: Some of the Bloodsailors prefer working for him, and I think it's getting to the point where he's going to challenge Vengaul.
Text: 핏빛 항해자 중 일부는 그 밑에서 일하는 걸 선호하고, 벵골에게 도전할 지경에 이른 것 같소.

TextEng: Oh, the Vengaul I know likes confrontation. He wouldn't run from a fight. I think whatever was supposed to happen up here has been changed.
Text: 오, 내가 아는 벵골은 대결을 좋아하오. 싸움에서 도망치지 않을 거요. 여기서 일어나기로 한 일이 바뀐 것 같소.

TextEng: Ain't my business, like I said, but I saw some of Callik's boys going downstairs, and now the basement is locked up tight.
Text: 말했듯이 내 일이 아니지만, 칼릭 부하들이 아래층으로 가는 걸 봤고, 지금 지하실은 꽁꽁 잠겨 있소.

TextEng: Something is going on... I just don't know what.
Text: 뭔가 벌어지고 있소... 뭔지 모르겠지만.

TextEng: Callik is pretty powerful right now. A lot of the Bloodsailors wouldn't mind making a little more profit instead of playing for show.
Text: 칼릭은 지금 꽤 강력하오. 핏빛 항해자 상당수가 쇼하는 대신 좀 더 이익을 내는 것에 반대하지 않을 거요.

TextEng: In fact, Callik has taken over running the black market. He's one of the few guys I've seen with a key to get downstairs.
Text: 사실, 칼릭이 암시장 운영을 맡았소. 아래층으로 내려가는 열쇠를 가진 몇 안 되는 사람 중 하나요.

TextEng: I thought he'd be here. Not like him to sit in his house while something is happening. He'd really like to embarrass Vengaul.
Text: 그가 여기 있을 줄 알았소. 뭔가 벌어지는데 집에 앉아 있을 사람이 아니거든. 벵골을 망신 주고 싶어할 거요.

TextEng: Hmm? I think it was in the far northeast corner of the district. I wouldn't go poking around there, though. Not unless you want trouble.
Text: 흠? 지구의 북동쪽 끝 구석에 있었던 것 같소. 하지만 거기 기웃거리진 않겠소. 문제 원하지 않는 한.

TextEng: Ah, I got no reason to talk. No more auction, no more fighting. Nothing happening now, so you might as well leave me be.
Text: 아, 말할 이유가 없소. 경매도 없고, 싸움도 없고. 지금은 아무 일도 없으니, 날 내버려두시오.
